ed}BC^{2}+AC^{2}&amp;=3DAB\times BH+AB\times AH\\&amp;=3DAB(AH+BH),\end{ali=
gned}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8f0d81ec566fb344a8f34b0acebb1ba835ce9fde" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -2.505ex; width:39.071ex; height:6.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {=
\begin{aligned}BC^{2}+AC^{2}&amp;=3DAB\times BH+AB\times AH\\&amp;=3DAB(AH+=
BH),\end{aligned}}}"></span>
which, after simplification, demonstrates the Pythagorean theorem:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
