r" style=3D"font-style:italic;">D</span>, then <span class=3D"texhtml mvar"=
 style=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> also increases by <span class=3D"tex=
html mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">dy</span>. These form two sides of =
a triangle, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">CDE</=
span>, which (with <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;=
">E</span> chosen so <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:itali=
c;">CE</span> is perpendicular to the hypotenuse) is a right triangle appro=
ximately similar to <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic=
;">ABC</span>. Therefore, the ratios of their sides must be the same, that =
is:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
