l-align: -0.838ex; width:35.947ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle \=
operatorname {sgn} (\alpha +\beta -\gamma )=3D\operatorname {sgn} (a^{2}+b^=
{2}-c^{2}),}"></span>
where <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B1</spa=
n> is the angle opposite to side <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font=
-style:italic;">a</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:=
italic;">=CE=B2</span> is the angle opposite to side <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">b</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B3</span> is the angle opposite to side <s=
pan class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">c</span>, and sgn i=
