"Quadratic irrational">Quadratic irrational</a>.
</p><p>Incommensurable lengths conflicted with the Pythagorean school's con=
cept of numbers as only whole numbers. The Pythagorean school dealt with pr=
oportions by comparison of integer multiples of a common subunit.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-Lavine0_34-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem#cite_note-Lavine0-34"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>33<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> According t=
o one legend, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hippasus" title=3D"H=
ippasus">Hippasus of Metapontum</a> (<abbr title=3D"circa">c.</abbr><span s=
tyle=3D"white-space:nowrap;">=E2=80=89470&nbsp;BC</span>) was drowned at se=
a for making known the existence of the irrational or incommensurable.<sup =
id=3D"cite_ref-drown_35-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem#cite_note-drown-35"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kurt_von_Fritz" title=3D"Kurt von =
Fritz">Kurt von Fritz</a> wrote a careful discussion of Hippasus's contribu=
tions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEFritz1945_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem#cite_note-FOOTNOTEF=
ritz1945-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>35<span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Complex_numbers">Complex nu=
