<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Euclidean_distance">Euclide=
an distance</h3></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_distance" =
title=3D"Euclidean distance">Euclidean distance</a></div>
<p>The distance formula in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartesi=
an_coordinates" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cartesian coordinates">Carte=
sian coordinates</a> is derived from the Pythagorean theorem.<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-Macdonald_37-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem#cite_note-Macdonald-37"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>36<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> If <span cl=
ass=3D"texhtml">(<i>x</i><sub>1</sub>, <i>y</i><sub>1</sub>)</span> and <sp=
an class=3D"texhtml">(<i>x</i><sub>2</sub>, <i>y</i><sub>2</sub>)</span> ar=
e points in the plane, then the distance between them, also called the <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_distance" title=3D"Euclidean=
 distance">Euclidean distance</a>, is given by
</p><p><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=
=3D"mwe-math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math display=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttex=
t=3D"{\displaystyle {\sqrt {(x_{1}-x_{2})^{2}+(y_{1}-y_{2})^{2}}}.}">
  <semantics>
