ata-file-height=3D"408"></a><figcaption>Similar right triangles showing sin=
e and cosine of angle =CE=B8</figcaption></figure>
<p>In a right triangle with sides <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fon=
t-style:italic;">a</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style=
:italic;">b</span> and hypotenuse <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fon=
t-style:italic;">c</span>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trigono=
metry" title=3D"Trigonometry">trigonometry</a> determines the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sine" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Sine">sine=
</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cosine" class=3D"mw-redir=
ect" title=3D"Cosine">cosine</a> of the angle <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">=CE=B8</span> between side <span class=3D"texh=
tml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">a</span> and the hypotenuse as:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle \sin \theta =3D{\frac {b}{c}},\quad \cos \theta =3D{\frac {a}{c=
}}.}">
