s=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup=
> In similar triangles, the ratios of the sides are the same regardless of =
the size of the triangles, and depend upon the angles. Consequently, in the=
 figure, the triangle with hypotenuse of unit size has opposite side of siz=
e <span class=3D"texhtml">sin <i>=CE=B8</i></span> and adjacent side of siz=
e <span class=3D"texhtml">cos <i>=CE=B8</i></span> in units of the hypotenu=
se.
</p>
