class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + <i>B</i> =3D <i>C</i></span>.
</p><p>Conversely, if we can prove that <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + =
<i>B</i> =3D <i>C</i></span> for three similar figures without using the Py=
thagorean theorem, then we can work backwards to construct a proof of the t=
heorem. For example, the starting center triangle can be replicated and use=
d as a triangle <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">C=
