altitude</a>. The sum of the areas of the two smaller triangles therefore i=
s that of the third, thus <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>A</i> + <i>B</i> =3D <=
i>C</i></span> and reversing the above logic leads to the Pythagorean theor=
