<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Sets_of_m-dimensional_objec=
ts_in_n-dimensional_space">Sets of <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"fo=
nt-style:italic;">m</span>-dimensional objects in <span class=3D"texhtml mv=
ar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>-dimensional space</h3></div>
<p>Another generalization of the Pythagorean theorem applies to <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lebesgue-measurable" class=3D"mw-redirect" ti=
tle=3D"Lebesgue-measurable">Lebesgue-measurable</a> sets of objects in any =
number of dimensions. Specifically, the square of the measure of an <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>-dimensional set=
 of objects in one or more parallel <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"f=
ont-style:italic;">m</span>-dimensional <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Flat_(geometry)" title=3D"Flat (geometry)">flats</a> in <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</span>-dimensional <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_space" title=3D"Euclidean space=
">Euclidean space</a> is equal to the sum of the squares of the measures of=
 the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthogonality" title=3D"Ortho=
gonality">orthogonal</a> projections of the object(s) onto all <span class=
=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">m</span>-dimensional coordin=
