ata-file-height=3D"520"></a><figcaption>Distance between infinitesimally se=
parated points in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cartesian_coordi=
nates" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Cartesian coordinates">Cartesian coor=
dinates</a> (top) and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polar_coordi=
nates" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Polar coordinates">polar coordinates<=
/a> (bottom), as given by Pythagoras's theorem</figcaption></figure>
<p>The Pythagorean theorem applies to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Differential_(mathematics)" title=3D"Differential (mathematics)">infini=
tesimal</a> triangles seen in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diff=
erential_geometry" title=3D"Differential geometry">differential geometry</a=
>. In three dimensional space, the distance between two infinitesimally sep=
arated points satisfies
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle ds^{2}=3Ddx^{2}+dy^{2}+dz^{2},}">
