e:italic;">dy</span>, <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:ital=
ic;">dz</span>) the components of the vector separating the two points. Suc=
h a space is called a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_sp=
ace" title=3D"Euclidean space">Euclidean space</a>. However, in <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemannian_geometry" title=3D"Riemannian geom=
etry">Riemannian geometry</a>, a generalization of this expression useful f=
or general coordinates (not just Cartesian) and general spaces (not just Eu=
clidean) takes the form:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Chow_67-0" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pythagorean_theorem#cite_note-Chow=
-67"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>66<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup>
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle ds^{2}=3D\sum _{i,j}^{n}g_{ij}\,dx_{i}\,dx_{j}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>d</mi>
        <msup>
