et">[</span>b<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> It may be a fu=
nction of position, and often describes <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Curved_space" title=3D"Curved space">curved space</a>. A simple examp=
le is Euclidean (flat) space expressed in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Curvilinear_coordinates" title=3D"Curvilinear coordinates">curvilin=
ear coordinates</a>. For example, in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Polar_coordinates" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Polar coordinates">pol=
ar coordinates</a>:
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
splay=3D"block" xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\d=
isplaystyle ds^{2}=3Ddr^{2}+r^{2}d\theta ^{2}.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>d</mi>
        <msup>
          <mi>s</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
